# 1. さらなる躍進のために

Airi: *Sigh* Another day, another tough shoot!
Shizuku: But it ended up being a lot of fun. I never thought I'd get to be the one pulling a prank on people.
Minori: Me neither. My heart wouldn't stop racing during the entire thing!
Minori: Unfortunately... Our prank didn't go that well.
Haruka: Yeah. Replacing all the ghosts in that amusement park's haunted house with idols seemed like a good idea, but...
Haruka: Shizuku was acting so suspiciously that everyone figured out who she was, and our prank sort of ended up turning into a meet and greet.
Shizuku: While you all did such a good job of being ghastly ghosts and spooky spirits that no one noticed who you were.
Airi: To be fair, the production teams are always prepared for these things with shows that involve a lot of pranks...
Airi: Anyway, the producer really seemed to enjoy it, so I'm calling it a job well done!
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm really glad.
Shizuku: And it's so nice how we've been getting invited onto all these different programs lately.
Haruka: Yeah. They've mostly been online and local programs, but it definitely feels like people are noticing us more.
Haruka: So, let's keep up the good work.
Minori: Right! So we can do a show at the Dome!
Airi: Us doing a show at the Dome's still way off in the future, so let's just keep trying to accomplish what we can for now.
Shizuku: What we can for now... Our next goal is to perform at the Butokan, yes?
Haruka: Yeah, and it seats 15,000... We've been getting a lot more media attention lately, so I feel like we're making good progress...
Haruka: But how many people do you think would show up if we made an announcement right now?
Airi: We have a lot more subscribers and followers online now, but getting people to physically come if we actually did it is a different story.
Minori: If we actually did it...
Minori: Then, why don't we?!
Shizuku: What?
Minori: If we just did one, then we'd know exactly where we're at in terms of how many people we can attract, right...?
Minori: Plus, we've been getting a lot of comments asking about when our next show's gonna be! I have a feeling everyone's already really excited about it!
Haruka: Yeah, and it has been a little while since our solo show.
Airi: True. And it'd be nice to see everyone's faces again...
Airi: Alright, let's start planning for it!
Minori: Woohoo!!
Shizuku: Oh, that means we'll need to find a venue, come up with a set list and such...
Minori: Yeah, right! Since we're doing this, we should do something that'll blow everyone's minds! Any ideas?
Haruka: As much as I want to keep discussing this, it's getting pretty late, and we're all tired from work...
Airi: Yeah... Let's head home for now. We'll discuss this again another time after we've had a chance to come up with ideas!
Shizuku: Okay!
Saito: I see... So that's why you asked me to join you today.
Haruka: Yes. We thought that it'd be best to ask you for advice regarding our ideas for the show and how to run the venue.
Shizuku: We hammered out a list of things that we'd like to do now, but we're not sure how practical they're going to be. So, we were hoping to get a second opinion.
Saito: I'll be more than glad to help! Please give me a moment to read through this document of yours!
Saito: Let's see...
Saito: These all sound like really great ideas! It shouldn't be hard to do them!
Shizuku: Thank goodness...
Saito: However, Minori, your “gifts for everyone” idea might hurt your budget a bit...
Saito: Not too long ago, this would've been pretty easy to pull off. But now, MORE MORE JUMP! has a lot more fans...
Saito: Footing the bill for enough gifts to hand out to everyone you meet is already going to be pretty tough. On top of that, the crowd may become a bit chaotic.
Saito: Which means you'd have to hire more staff and security. In other words, higher costs.
Minori: Th-That's right! All the big idol events have tons and tons of security!
Minori: I never thought that we'd ever have to need that much security at one of our events...
Airi: We trust our fans to behave themselves, but we do need to have a plan in place just in case.
Haruka: Right... It's always fun to directly interact with our fans, but those kinds of events come with certain risks.
Minori: I know our safety is important, but I also don't want any of our fans to get hurt!
Shizuku: I agree. We should do what we can to ensure that everyone who comes to see us has a good time.
Saito: Still, I'm sure your guests would be over the moon to receive a gift from MMJ! So, if you can stay within budget, I say go for it.
Saito: Since you haven't picked a venue yet, you can book one first and see what you're going to have left before deciding what to do.
Minori: I see...
Airi: Thanks for always giving us such detailed advice, Saito! We really appreciate it!
Saito: No, I'm only able to say these things because I was recently involved in helping put together a fairly involved event. I'm just glad to put that experience to good use!
Shizuku: I don't know what to say. I'm starting to feel bad about always receiving so much wonderful advice from you.
Haruka: That's not limited to just events. You've been giving us all sorts of good advice regarding our schedule after we started appearing on TV.
Haruka: So, thank you very much for all your help.
Saito: No, um... I feel honored that I get to help with the operations of MORE MORE JUMP!
Saito: And I became so excited when I heard that you'd be doing another event...!
Saito: Oh, look at me... I'm babbling away about how I feel as a fan.
Airi: Hehe. And we couldn't be more grateful.
Saito: Anyway, that's enough of my fangirling. Let's get back to discussing your event!
Saito: As I mentioned a moment ago, I suggest that you all start by looking for your next venue.
Saito: Are there any that happen to immediately come to mind? If so, I can ask to see if they'll be available.
Minori: Oh, that'd help so much!
Minori: So, we were actually in the middle of deciding where we can do this...
Shizuku: The thing is, we have quite a lot on our plate at the moment.
Shizuku: Our original goal for today was to find a good date for our next event and see which venues are available while looking at our current schedule.
Saito: Yes, I see! In that case... Would you mind showing me your current schedule?
Haruka: Yes, of course. This is what it looks like right now...
Saito: Wow...! Busy is right! You're all booked up for the next few months...
Saito: Oh, hang on...
Haruka: Did you find something?
Saito: Oh, it's just... About what you have planned for Friday on this week here...
Saito: This meeting for FluffTalk is scheduled to end not long before your interview with LoVE IDoL is supposed to begin.
Saito: You're supposed to meet in Akasaka for FluffTalk, but Yokohama for LoVE IDoL... Will you be able to make it to this interview in time?
Minori: What...?!
Airi: She's right... Our FluffTalk meeting ends at seven and that interview for LoVE IDoL starts at eight. Which means...
Shizuku: We're only going to have about an hour to get from Akasaka to Yokohama. It's usually around forty minutes by train...
Shizuku: And we run the risk of being late if we get lost or anything else happens.
Haruka: Yeah... And that's assuming this meeting actually ends right at seven. We'll be cutting it really close.
Airi: I'm so sorry. It's my fault for penciling in both. I'll call them right away to see if we can change the meeting time.
Shizuku: Airi...
Airi: Phew... It's still some time away, so they were happy to meet at a different time...
Shizuku: What a relief...
Airi: Again, I'm really sorry. I caused you all stress over something I did.
Haruka: No, don't say that. It's our fault for leaving it all to you.
Minori: We can check over everything together next time!
Haruka: Right. It's always good to have another set of eyes look over everything.
Airi: I'd really appreciate it. Still...
Airi: We would've been in huge trouble if you hadn't caught this just now, Saito. I don't even know how to begin thanking you...
Saito: No, I just happened to notice is all... It was nothing, really.
Saito: Still, managing such a packed schedule all by yourselves seems like a tall order.
Airi: It is. I'm not gonna lie, I've sort of been at my wit's end for a little while now... My hope is that we'll be able to hire a manager soon.
Airi: But that means looking for the right person for the job and figuring out how to actually go about hiring them. We just haven't had the time.
Saito: Yes, I see... Especially considering how busy you all are right now.
Haruka: Also, we're not a company or anything, so we wouldn't be able to hire them as our employee per se.
Haruka: Which basically means we'd be taking them on as a freelancer... I'm not sure how many people we'll find who are willing to work under those conditions.
Minori: Th-That's true...
Airi: On the other hand, we want someone we can trust and who understands who we are as a group.
Minori: Th-That's also true...!
Airi: As a result, we haven't really been able to get ourselves to start looking for someone.
Saito: I see...
Shizuku: (Someone we can trust... Someone who understands who we are...)
Shizuku: (Who's also suited to the job of a manager...)
Shizuku: (Wait a second...)
Shizuku: Saito, aren't you the perfect choice?
Saito: What...?
Shizuku: You've been supporting us all this time, giving us so much wonderful advice and being so reliable.
Shizuku: You even immediately saw a problem with our schedule after having only a quick glance at it.
Shizuku: I honestly believe no one else is more well-suited for this job than you.
Saito: M...
Saito: M-Me...?!
